{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at a module handoff: changed-file discovery -> analysis scheduler. A unit test of just a filter function would miss wiring bugs where unchanged files are still dispatched. System was considered but rejected because this behavior can be validated with in-process fixtures/fakes for changed-file lists and file inventory; no real OS/network/subprocess behavior is required by the behavior text.","test_description":"Run the lint step with a fake changed-files provider and a mixed repository fixture, then assert only changed paths are sent to analysis and unchanged paths are never scanned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This checks interaction between findings aggregation, severity bucketing, and PR comment rendering/posting. Unit tests of formatter logic alone can miss miswired severity mapping across modules. System was considered but rejected: behavior text is about grouping content, not real GitHub HTTP behavior; a fake PR client is sufficient.","test_description":"Feed mixed-severity findings through the real pipeline modules up to comment publish boundary using a fake GitHub client, and assert the emitted comment body has correct error/warning/info groups and membership.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real runtime/throughput constraint tied to GitHub Actions timeout behavior. Mocks hide true performance bottlenecks (process startup, I/O, scheduling, runner limits). Integration was considered and rejected because the behavior explicitly requires meeting the Actions timeout in realistic execution conditions.","test_description":"Execute the lint job end-to-end in a CI-like runner against a 200-file fixture using the real analysis execution path, and assert wall-clock completion under 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly references a crashing linter process, which is a subprocess/OS failure boundary. Simulated in-process exceptions can miss real crash semantics and process-exit handling. Integration was considered and rejected due to concrete text: 'linter process crashes' requires real subprocess failure handling.","test_description":"Run analysis with a real subprocess invocation where one malformed file triggers a linter crash/abnormal exit, then verify pipeline continues processing other files and still publishes consolidated results.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is primarily deterministic dedup logic over finding records (same file/line/rule overlap). The failure can be reproduced and caught within one local function/object boundary with no I/O. Higher levels were considered but rejected: behavior text does not require real OS/network/subprocess or LLM output, and no mandatory cross-module invariant is stated.","test_description":"Provide a findings list containing intentional same-line duplicates from overlapping rules to the dedup function and assert exactly one output entry per dedup key.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
